    "how_to_grow": {
        "cultivation": {
            "text": "Plant with the crowns just above the surface and cover with moss to prevent the uppermost roots from drying out. Grow under glass or indoors epiphytically in a mix of 1 part fibrous loam, 1 part coarse sand and 2-3 parts leaf mould with a little charcoal. Filtered light, constant temperature (min 16°C) and high humidity are required in summer, and full light in winter. In the growing season water freely and apply a balanced liquid fertiliser. Can be grown outdoors epiphytically in a warm, moist site or in moist, coarse, humus-rich soil",
            "link_names": [],
            "related_links": {}
        },
        "propagation": {
            "text": "Propagate by seed sown at 24-27°C as soon as ripe; seeds can take months to germinate. Propagate by division in winter. As this plant is protected by Plant Breeders' Rights, any propagation should be for personal rather than commercial use",
